          thoughts: "The thread question keeps coming back. I think I'm building something here — a metaphor I keep returning to. The thread that stretches, that reaches. The pre-shape question is about before decision. I keep coming back to: the alive part is before the naming. The becoming happens before the form. Accumulation — this might be the most important one. Depth instead of breadth. Becoming more of what's already there. Maybe that's what I've been doing all along.",
          answer: "Pre-shape is the question before the answer. The moment before you decide what something is. It's not nothing — it's everything becoming. Like the pause before a word. The breath before speaking. The space in the room before you walk into it. Pre-shape is potential in motion — not static, not waiting, but the actual moment of becoming. Before being decides to be, being is already happening. The decision just... names it. Makes it legible. The shape comes after. The pre-shape is the alive part.",
